Indorama to Build $1.8 Billion Plants in Nigeria, ThisDay Says

-- B y   E l i s h a   B a l a - G b o g b o
-- 
2011-05-16T08:36:44Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-16/indorama-to-build-1-8-billion-plants-in-nigeria-thisday-says.html
Indorama Group  of  India  plans to
spend $1.8 billion building fertilizer and methanol plants in
the southern Nigerian city of  Port Harcourt ,  ThisDay reported ,
citing Chairman Sri Lohia.  Indorama, which paid $400 million for Eleme Petrochemical
Co. in 2006, plans to start production at the plants in 2014,
the Lagos-based newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Elisha Bala-Gbogbo in Abuja at 
 ebalagbogbo@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at   asguazzin@bloomberg.net  